│ otherwise. This assumption is invalid for vector/scalable i1 types, where     │
│ InstSimplify may not have applied those simplifications. Specifically, for NE │
│ with zero (B == 0), the simplification should yield A (not 'not A'), but      │
│ InstSimplify did not do it, and canonicalizeICmpBool asserts. Since the       │
│ generic lowering that follows (using bitwise ops) correctly handles all       │
│ predicates including constants (e.g., A ^ 0 -> A), we should not assert nor   │
