│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash occurs in canonicalizeICmpBool() due to an llvm_unreachable         │
│ triggered when handling boolean compares against constants. The function      │
│ assumes that InstSimplify has already folded certain boolean-constant cases   │
│ (the ones that do not simplify to 'not A'), and therefore asserts if it       │
│ encounters them. In the reproducer, we have a scalable vector of i1: icmp ne  │
│ <vscale x 8 x i1> A, zeroinitializer. InstSimplify did not fold this vector   │
│ case prior to canonicalization, so canonicalizeICmpBool sees NE with zero and │
│ hits the unreachable path.                                                    │
